author: kirotv.com
title: Deputies say teens crashed stolen car, disposed of gun
text:
King County sheriff’s deputies caught four teenagers early Wednesday morning after some of them ran from a stolen car they had crashed in Burien.
A sheriff’s spokesperson said one boy was injured at the scene, while another boy was quickly caught. King County Guardian One was able to locate the two girls, who were hiding behind parked cars in the neighborhood.
Deputies found a magazine for a gun inside the car and found a gun on the front lawn of a house near where the girls were hiding.
Neighbors were startled as they awoke to the sound of the stolen car crashing into a fence and knocking over a mailbox.
